main event: Unidentified flying object sighted by the Coast Guard Cutter Sebago in the Gulf of Mexico on November 5, 1957.
interesting points: The UFO was tracked on radar moving from north to south at a high rate of speed., Visual contact was held for approximately three seconds., The object appeared circular and grayish-white in color., Despite multiple radar sightings, only one object was initially believed to be present., It was determined that visual contact was likely a meteor and radar signals may have been affected by erroneous propagation.
witness description: Coast Guard personnel operated under radar observations.
